Umar Muhammed, Lafia About 12 suspected kidnappers who abducted the Permanent Secretary, Nasarawa State Ministry of Works, Mr Jibrin Giza, have been apprehended. While parading the suspects on Wednesday in Lafia, the state Commissioner of Police, Mr Bola Longe, said five suspected kidnappers were arrested between Nasarawa Eggon Local Government Area and Shabu area of the Lafia East Development Area of the state on Tuesday. The police boss further revealed that the personnel of the command also apprehended about seven of the kidnap suspects at Duduguru area of the state. He explained, “The permanent secretary was kidnapped on Sunday morning at about 12:40 am. We mobilised our personnel to all nooks and crannies of the state.” Copyright PUNCH.
